# LYONiX Monad

**A lightweight cryptographic provenance engine built from Geometry.**

I am not a professional developer. What I understand deeply is a certain **Geometry** — a mathematical structure that elegantly handles order, time, identity, and relationships.

Using AI assistance, I turned this Geometry into a working prototype called the **LYONiX Monad**.

### Core Purpose
The Monad creates tamper-proof records of digital content with:
- Cryptographic fingerprints (SHA-256)
- Temporal sequencing (what came first)
- Derivative detection
- A compliance-style hash that proves sources were documented — without exposing the actual data

This is particularly relevant for AI companies facing regulatory requirements (EU AI Act, California TDTA, GDPR) who need honest provenance while protecting trade secrets.

### Demo

This repository contains a clean single-file demo (`lyonix_demo.py`) that demonstrates the main ideas.

### How to Run

```bash
git clone https://github.com/ErikLYONiX/lyonix-suite.git
cd lyonix-suite

pip install numpy
python lyonix_demo.py